{"type": "ssml","ssml": "<speak>Who has returned from an area where Covid 19 is spreading should monitor themselves for symptoms for 14 days and take their temperature twice a day. This means avoiding close contact (one meter or nearer) with other people, including family members. You should also telephone your healthcare provider or the local public health department, giving them details of your recent travel and symptoms.</speak>"}

{"type": "ssml","ssml": "<speak>The virus that causes Covid 19 and the one that causes Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome are related to each other genetically, but they are different. SARS is more deadly but much less infectious than Covid 19. There have been no outbreaks of SARS anywhere in the world since 2003.</speak>"}

{"type": "ssml","ssml": "<speak>In the event of a suspected case, special safety criteria are applied, which are recommended by the Ministry of Health in consultation with experts and specialists and derived from international guidelines. A sick person is isolated, contact persons are identified, informed and, depending on the situation, can be quarantined, for example. All measures aim to ensure that as few people as possible are infected by the pathogen.</speak>"}

{"type": "ssml","ssml": "<speak>Experiences from previous outbreaks of related coronaviruses, such as the Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome coronavirus and Middle East respiratory syndrome coronavirus show that transmission through food consumption did not occur. To date, there have not been any reports of transmission of SARS CoV 2 virus through food, however, concerns were expressed about the potential for these viruses to persist on raw foods of animal origin.</speak>"}

{"type": "ssml","ssml": "<speak>The report of the WHO-China Joint Mission on Coronavirus Disease 2019 states that mild cases have an average course of two weeks and severe cases 3-6 weeks.</speak>"}

{"type": "ssml","ssml": "<speak>The United Nations predicts that the world economy will contract by almost one percent this year because of the new coronavirus pandemic, instead of growing by 2.5 percent as predicted.</speak>"}

{"type": "ssml","ssml": "<speak>A pandemic is the worldwide spread of a new disease and occurs when a new virus emerges and spreads around the world, and most people do not have immunity. Viruses that have caused past pandemics typically originated from animal influenza viruses.</speak>"}

{"type": "ssml","ssml": "<speak>Preliminary findings indicate that the mortality rate for Covid 19 is twenty to thirty per thousand people diagnosed. This is significantly less than the 2003 SARS outbreak. However, it is much higher than the mortality rate for seasonal influenza.</speak>"}

{"type": "ssml","ssml": "<speak>Unfortunately, it is not possible to predict how long the outbreak will last and how the epidemic will unfold. We are dealing with a new virus and therefore a lot of uncertainty remains. For instance, it is not known whether transmission within the EU/EEA will naturally decrease during the northern hemisphere summer, as is observed for seasonal influenza.</speak>"}

{"type":"hints","options":[{"label":"About COVID-19","value":"About COVID-19"},{"label":"Preventive Measures","value":"Preventive Measures"},{"label":"Transmission","value":"Transmission"},{"label":"Symptoms","value":"Symptoms"}]}

{"type": "ssml","ssml": "<speak>It is too early to know how long the protective immune response against SARS CoV 2 will last, as this will require longitudinal serological studies that follow patients’ immunity over an extended period of time. Evidence from other coronavirus infections, like SARS and MERS, indicates that immunity may last for up to three years and re-infection with the same strain of seasonal circulating coronavirus is highly unlikely in the same or following season. This could also hold true for SARS CoV 2 as there is emerging evidence from early studies suggesting that individuals develop antibodies after infection and are likely to be immune from reinfection in the short term.</speak>"}

{"type": "ssml","ssml": "<speak>Data on the progression of the disease is available from a limited number of reported hospitalized cases. Based on available information, the median time from symptom onset to laboratory confirmation nationally decreased from 12 days in early January to 3 days by early February 2020, and in Wuhan from 15 days to 5 days, respectively. This has allowed for earlier case and contact identification, isolation and treatment.</speak>"}

{"type": "ssml","ssml": "<speak>It is quite normal for people to worry about how the Covid 19 outbreak will affect them and their loved ones. We can channel our concerns into actions to protect ourselves, our loved ones and our communities.</speak>"}
{"type":"hints","options":[{"label":"Preventive Measures","value":"Preventive Measures"},{"label":"Transmission","value":"Transmission"},{"label":"Symptoms","value":"Symptoms"}]}

{"type": "ssml","ssml": "<speak>In light of current knowledge, coronaviruses are not sexually transmitted. However, it is possible to transmit the coronavirus during sexual activity, especially if self-care measures to prevent virus transmission are not followed. Take care when giving kisses and with close facial contacts and avoid occasional sexual encounters or with people who are sick with respiratory symptoms.</speak>"}

{"type": "ssml","ssml": "<speak>Severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2 or SARS Cov 2 is the name of the new virus because it is genetically related to the coronavirus responsible for the SARS outbreak of 2003. Covid 19 is the name of this new disease, following guidelines previously developed with the World Organisation for Animal Health and the Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations.</speak>"}

{"type":"hints","options":[{"label":"About COVID-19","value":"About COVID-19"},{"label":"Preventive Measures","value":"Preventive Measures"},{"label":"Transmission","value":"Transmission"},{"label":"Symptoms","value":"Symptoms"}]}

{"type": "ssml","ssml": "<speak>Covid 19 is the infectious disease caused by the most recently discovered coronavirus. This new virus and disease were unknown before the outbreak began in Wuhan, China, in December 2019. Covid 19 is now a pandemic affecting many countries globally.</speak>"}

{"type":"hints","options":[{"label":"Preventive Measures","value":"Preventive Measures"},{"label":"Transmission","value":"Transmission"},{"label":"Symptoms","value":"Symptoms"},{"label":"World Situation","value":"World Situation"}]}

{"type": "ssml","ssml": "<speak>Both Covid 19 and influenza viruses cause respiratory disease and are transmitted by contact, droplets and fomites. The serial interval for Covid 19 virus is estimated to be 5-6 days, while for influenza virus, the serial interval is 3 days. This means that influenza can spread faster than Covid 19. Although similar, mortality for Covid 19 appears higher than for influenza, especially seasonal influenza.</speak>"}

{"type":"hints","options":[{"label":"About COVID-19","value":"About COVID-19"},{"label":"Preventive Measures","value":"Preventive Measures"},{"label":"Transmission","value":"Transmission"},{"label":"Symptoms","value":"Symptoms"}]}

{"type": "ssml","ssml": "<speak>There is not enough epidemiological information at this time to determine how easily and sustainably this virus spreads between people, but it is currently estimated that, on average, one infected person will infect between two and three more.</speak>"}

{"type": "ssml","ssml": "<speak>On 31 December 2019, the Wuhan Municipal Health Commission in Wuhan City, Hubei province, China, reported a cluster of 27 pneumonia cases (including seven severe cases) of unknown aetiology, with a common reported link to Wuhan's Huanan Seafood Wholesale Market, a wholesale fish and live animal market. The market was closed down on 1 January 2020. According to the Wuhan Municipal Health Commission, samples from the market tested positive for novel coronavirus. Cases showed symptoms such as fever, dry cough, dyspnoea; radiological findings showed bilateral lung infiltrates.</speak>"}

{"type": "ssml","ssml": "<speak>Coronaviruses are a large family of viruses which may cause respiratory infections ranging from the common cold to more severe diseases such as Middle East Respiratory Syndrome and Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome. The most recently discovered coronavirus causes coronavirus disease Covid 19.</speak>"}

People can also catch Covid 19 if they breathe in droplets from a person with Covid 19 who coughs out or exhales droplets.</speak>"}

{"type": "ssml","ssml": "<speak>Anyone can help contain the further spread of the novel coronavirus by staying home and keeping physical contact to a minimum. This is necessary to protect risk groups and reduce the burden in hospitals as much as possible. How long this situation can continue is still uncertain. But we can certainly reduce the duration by staying at home consistently.</speak>"}

{"type": "ssml","ssml": "<speak>Persons who are infected, have had contact with infected persons or have stayed in risk areas are officially ordered a 14-day quarantine. During this period, the Robert Koch Institute recommends that those affected must take their temperature twice a day, keep a diary of their symptoms, take swabs on request and be available to the staff of the public health department. They are to report to the sick person daily. Persons who have not been quarantined must nevertheless observe the ban on contact. Violations of the contact restrictions should be monitored by the regulatory authorities and the police and sanctions should be imposed in the event of violations.</speak>"}

{"type": "ssml","ssml": "<speak>Customers behave irrationally because they make panic purchases that are not necessary for fear of a shortage of goods. This includes toilet paper. However, the supply of goods is absolutely guaranteed. Often the employees simply could not keep up with refilling the shelves fast enough.</speak>"}

{"type": "ssml","ssml": "<speak>Persons infected with the virus must not leave the quarantine. This also means that they should not take the dog into the streets or parks. However, if the person has their own house, they are allowed to move around on your property with the dog. However, social contacts may not be perceived even in this case. If the person is not infected, walks with the dog are allowed. Keep a distance of at least 1-2 metres to other people outside.</speak>"}

{"type": "ssml","ssml": "<speak>Wash your hands regularly and thoroughly and follow the cough and sneeze label. Avoid touching your face. Keep a minimum distance of 2 metres from other people and avoid hugs, kisses, handshakes, etc. Do not leave your home unless absolutely necessary. Therefore, refrain from any kind of social events. If it is absolutely necessary to leave the house, avoid public transport as far as possible. Ask your employer for home work. And last but not least: Don't panic!</speak>"}

{"type": "ssml","ssml": "<speak>Anyone who has been ordered into quarantine because they are infected or at risk of infection is obliged to stay at home and keep their distance from third parties. The person concerned must not leave the house for shopping or walking the dog. Relatives can support the contact person in everyday life, for example, by shopping.</speak>"}

{"type": "ssml","ssml": "<speak>Introducing quarantine measures early in an outbreak may delay the introduction of the disease to a country or area or may delay the peak of an epidemic in an area where local transmission is ongoing, or both. It is recommended that contacts of patients with laboratory-confirmed Covid 19 be quarantined for 14 days.</speak>"}

{"type": "ssml","ssml": "<speak>From the evidence so far, the Covid 19 virus can be transmitted in all areas, including areas with hot and humid weather. Regardless of climate, adopt protective measures if you live in, or travel to an area reporting Covid 19.</speak>"}

{"type": "ssml","ssml": "<speak>Garlic is a healthy food that may have some antimicrobial properties. However, there is no evidence from the current outbreak that eating garlic has protected people from the new coronavirus.</speak>"}

{"type": "ssml","ssml": "<speak>In times of Covid 19 spread, the increasing uncertainty and concern of people are the ideal breeding ground for conspiracy theories, false reports or myths. People often find out about the virus on various YouTube channels where online activists believe they know the true origin of the virus. False reports are also increasingly circulating via social media such as Facebook or WhatsApp. This can, for example, lead to increasing panic and panic buying. Therefore, please make sure that you only inform yourself on official websites such as those of the World Health Organization or the European Centre for Disease Prevention and Control.</speak>"}

{"type": "ssml","ssml": "<speak>Before putting on a mask it is important to clean hands with alcohol-based hand rub or soap and water. Inspect it for tears or holes. Finally pull down the mask’s bottom so it covers your mouth and your chin.</speak>"}
